comment:
I was brutally assaulted in 2011. I chose not to come forward because my family was dealing with my dad's declining health and I didn't want to add any stress to my family. I did tell a few of my very best friends - including one friend in an email (therefore time stamped "proof"). I also got my rapist to confess to the rape in a text in which he told me I, "wasn't woman enough to handle him anyway." This might not serve as tons of proof, but it's something.

However if I chose to come forward, I would want him to be imprisoned and I wouldn't care about money. Still, it would be very hard because many would blame me for not coming forward all this time. It's very hard for survivors as getting proof is damn near impossible and we're on this ticking clock to come forward immediately even if it's not possible for us to do so for many reasons.

Will all that being said, I believe that Amber needs to be behind bars immediately. She deserves 50+ years in prison because she not only lied about being assaulted by Johnny, she ruined his lucrative CAREER. While I suffer anxiety and PTSD, at least I can try to work. Johnny doesn't even have that option.

I believe countless REAL survivors who don't come forward right away but Amber isn't a survivor, she's a monster who needs to be locked up.

comment: I lived next-door to Johnny Depp for 14 years on Sunset Boulevard. I didn‚Äôt know him, we were just neighbors, but he would come over to our residence when the city put forth plans on putting up a building along the boulevard that would obstruct his view from his home which rested behind it. He would ask for us to please petition the city to not do so. It happened three times during that period, but each time he was very gracious and spent a considerable amount of his personal time chatting. We ran into each other at a few events because my partner was the president of the television Academy ( the Emmy Awards ) and although I never at all expected him to know my name or even really remember me, he‚Äôd give a nod and a smile and say ~ ‚ÄúI hope I‚Äôm not playing music too loud‚Äù Because the only time he would really spend a short stay at that home (I believe he primarily lived in France) was when he was either at an award show, in town promoting a film, or having just wrapped production on a film, in which he would have a three day celebration on his property, outside with a full concert venue and rock legends performing continuously through the night from dusk to dawn. Literally. It didn‚Äôt disturb anyone because it was right on the Sunset strip and his property rested far behind it on several acres. Having previously escaped from an abusive relationship, I was shocked at the allegations Amber placed against him and didn‚Äôt believe them for a moment. I work with victims of abuse and oils clearly see that he is, was, never an abuser. Watching Amber‚Äòs testimony it was clear who the real abuser was all along.

comment: I remember when the news first broke, everyone was quick to take Amber's side, and I saw a lot of posts about it. I commented on a now deleted Facebook post, saying the whole situation sounded pretty fishy. I did a little digging around, but I never really got too into the scoop, and I mentioned how even back then there were a few inconsistencies on Amber's side. I swear, if that post would have been an in person discussion, I would have been stoned to death. Everyone came at me, saying that I'm anti feminist and that I'm defending a monster (even though I didn't actually defend anybody in my comment). I was even told to kill myself. None of the comments fazed me, though, and I always stood by what I said since all I did was comment on one or two odd points. Eventually the post was deleted, and the poster has since gone on to realize (but not admit) she was wrong for supporting Amber and began only recently posting supportive messages to Johnny Depp and posts about boycotting Amber.

comment:
I have been following this, on and off, from the start. First was the accusations that were a little off. Many amateur sleuths quickly turned up evidence that not all was as AH stated. But that didn‚Äôt stop the self obsessed from declaring it it true because of nothing more then the gender of the accuser and accused( just like they were so quiet about AH‚Äôs past record because it didn‚Äôt fit the narrative).then came the knee jerk reactions, were JD was vilified and canceled by Disney and others. Not because of any facts, but on accusations that got more and more janky, even in the face of evidence that proved it unlikely, if not down right a lie. Yet still the hate for JD grew, more so as more amateur sleuths and court evidence, police reports and eye witnesses showed AH was not being truthful. It would be funny, if not for the physical and mental abuse JD went through, on how those who report to stand for victims of abuse all gathered to attack the victim and support the abuser. Showing that their rhetoric is just that, utter BS. That they do not care for what they claim, but instead use it as a weapon to attack on a purely gendered based ideology. 
And I will be surprised if AH actually serves jail time for abuse, and false accusations. She will get a slap on the wrist at most. It will be claimed she has ‚Äòsuffered‚Äô enough already, and her part in all this will be forgotten.
